tweet: .@Indiana_EDC, which expects these figures to grow, has been in conversation with more than 450 additional Hoosier companies that have pledged their assistance and are exploring ways to support PPE production and procurement as well as related services.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
➡️ Worldcell Extrusions (Elkhart County) has adjusted production to produce lightweight face shields for medical workers.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ Williams Distribution (Marion County), a minority-owned chemical distribution company in Indianapolis, is leveraging its expertise to support the increased need for PPE and is shipping nearly 48,000 items, including hand sanitizer, medical gowns and gloves, to the state.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ Top Stitch (Elkhart County), one of Indiana’s more than 508,000 small businesses, has applied its textile experience to the healthcare industry and is now making medical gowns and surgical face masks, filling orders to the state as well as to customers in the Northeast U.S.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ Tiedemann-Bevs Industries (Wayne County), has been operating in Richmond since 1974. TBI, which manufactures interior casket components and distributes essential textiles to hundreds of casket manufacturers in the industry, is now producing 1,000 isolation gowns per week.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ @superatvtweet (Jefferson County) has shifted production to make lightweight full face shields, intubation shields and retail employee protective barriers, with plans to produce face shields for the state’s front-line workers.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: Royer has partnered with Clifty Engineering, also based in Madison, to fabricate and build an additional die cutting machine, which will double its output of face shields.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ @RoyerCorp  (Jefferson County) is utilizing its resources to create face shields for medical workers. The Madison-based, family-owned company plans to produce 75,000 weekly pieces, sending 20,000 to support the state’s efforts so far.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ @MursixCorp (Delaware County) serves a wide range of customers whose applications range from hospital beds to automotive safety to hybrid electric vehicles. The Yorktown company is now manufacturing up to 500,000 face shields each week.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ Mastercraft (LaGrange County), the world’s largest maker of RV furniture, has been serving manufacturers and direct consumers since 1971. The LaGrange-based company is now using its expertise to manufacture non-medical isolation gowns, producing thousands each week.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ @jordanmfg (Newton & White Counties), has shifted production at its Indiana facilities in Monticello and Kentland to make isolation gowns to support healthcare providers, producing 11,500 for the state.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ Hentz Manufacturing's (Allen County) Fort Wayne facility has started production of isolation gowns, face masks and face shields and has already filled initial orders for the state. They have already produced 46,600 PPE items and is ramping up its team to meet demand.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ GDC Inc. (Elkhart County) plans to start manufacturing disposable full face shields in April and expects to provide 500,000 pieces to the state.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ @FleecePE (Hendricks County), has redeployed its engineers and a portion of its flexible manufacturing space to develop, test, document and begin producing lightweight disposable full face shields. The company now has the capacity to produce up to 250,000 per week.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ @Fatheadz (Marion County) has now shifted its operations to produce fluid protective goggles, safety glasses and shields and plans to fulfill an order of several thousand items to the state yet this week.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ @BerryGlobalInc (Vanderburgh County) is accelerating production of plastic face shields & aims to soon reach production of 150,000 per week. The company will provide 30,000 face shields to the state, helping provide an added protection for first responders & medical personnel.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ The Acid Products-Prairie Packaging Company (LaPorte County) is now helping meet demand for hand sanitizer and hard surface cleaners. The company’s Kingsbury facility is providing hand sanitizer to the state and also donated supplies to first responders in LaPorte County.

tweet:

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
➡️ The following individuals who are vulnerable and at higher risk for illness should not attend:

Persons who are 65 years and older.

Those who have severe underlying medical conditions, like heart or lung disease or diabetes.

Individuals who are sick.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
➡️ It is preferred that no communion be distributed.

In instances when communion is distributed, only prepackaged communion may be used and must be prepared and distributed in a manner that meets food safety standards.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
➡️ No one may exit a vehicle at any time.

➡️ Portable bathrooms are not allowed on the premises and no church facilities may be used by attendees.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
➡️ Vehicles should contain only members of a single household. Do not bring your neighbors or others outside of your household.

➡️ Cars must be spaced the equivalent of every other parking spot or approximately 9 feet apart.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
🚘 Drive-in services may be conducted only under these conditions:

➡️ Attendees must be inside vehicles at all times.

➡️ Attendees should not interact physically with clergy, staff or participants in other vehicles.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
➡️ Livestream or other virtual services are best.

The minimum number of necessary personnel should be used at all times for any services.

Staff and volunteers who are not speaking should wear masks.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
To continue safely serving their communities, faith institutions are directed as follows:

➡️ Church buildings and other physical locations for worship should be closed.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: Executive order 20-18 states all public and private gatherings, including religious and spiritual, should follow @CDCgov  guidance, which restricts gatherings to ten or less people. Click here to see executive orders:  https://www.in.gov/gov/2384.htm

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: The purpose of this guidance is not to restrict religious liberty, but to save lives during these extraordinary times. I look forward to the day where we can once again worship side-by-side without the threat of spreading coronavirus.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: During this time of uncertainty, faith is more important than ever, and I am deeply grateful to our religious leaders for their efforts to find safe and creative ways to serve their communities.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:

➡️ Advance Practice Registered Nurses are allowed to provide services in multiple locations.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️Other operational changes in branches are being instituted to provide for the safety of employees and customers in branches, such as spacing between terminals and limiting the number of customers in the lobby.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ The commissioner of the @INDeptInsurance will request that insurers institute a 60-day moratorium on policy cancellations for non-payment of premiums. This does not suspend a policyholder’s obligation to make payments.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:

➡️ Telehealth services for mental health, substance use disorder and prescribing for Medicaid covered services will be expanded.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:

➡️ Job search requirements are waived for those applying for Temporary Assistance to Needy Families (TANF) benefits.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ The Indiana Department of Financial Institutions and Indiana Community Housing Development Authority are required to work with financial institutions to identify tools to help promote housing stability.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ All public housing authorities are requested to extend deadlines for housing assistance recipients and required documentation to show eligibility for housing programs.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ No residential eviction proceedings or foreclosure actions may be initiated during the public health emergency. This does not relieve the individual of obligations to pay rent or mortgage payments.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ For employers, @WorkforceIND will not assess certain experience rate penalties because of employees who receive unemployment benefits because of #COVID19.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:

➡️ @WorkforceIND  will seek federal authorization to provide unemployment benefits for those who are not otherwise eligible for unemployment.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:

➡️ Benefits will be paid to individuals who file their initial unemployment claims late.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ The state’s application to the @SBAgov was approved on Wednesday. This program provides targeted, low-interest loans of up to $2 million to help small businesses and nonprofits overcome the temporary loss of revenue as a result of #coronavirus.  http://SBA.gov/Disaster .

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ Providers of essential utility services such as gas and electric, broadband, telecom, water and wastewater services are prohibited from discontinuing service to any customer during the public health emergency.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet: ➡️ The state will not immediately move forward w/ using $300 million in reserves to pay for several capital projects approved in the just-concluded legislative session & instead maintain flexibility to utilize the funds as needed for relief efforts & to maintain current services.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
➡️ Indiana will align w/ the federal government to delay state income tax payments from April 15 to July 15.

➡️ Penalties will be waived for 60 days for property tax paid after May 11. The state will work w/ counties that may experience cash flow stress because of the delay.

name: Governor Eric Holcomb
tweet:
➡️ I will extend the current state of emergency an additional 30 days when it expires on April 5.

➡️ All K-12 public schools will remain closed until May 1. Non-public schools are also ordered closed. 

➡️ All-state mandated assessments will be canceled for this academic year.
